  "notes": "Ligurian (Zenéize). Gallo-Italic language of Liguria. ~500,000 speakers. Reference variety: Genoese. Key features: (1) Front rounded vowels /y, ø/. (2) Nasal vowels (well-developed). (3) ⟨x⟩ = /ʒ/ (voiced postalveolar fricative, distinctive). (4) Degemination. Historical lingua franca of the Mediterranean maritime trade (Forner 1975).",
